Title: Shadows Cast By A Final Salute
Description: Defeat Captain Patricia to recover her Heartgem. Then retrieve her cloak of office from Slumbering Echoes. Talk to Watcher Sexton in the Eastburn Outpost when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I was hoping to see Captain Patricia, but I knew it would be too good to be true.\n\nShe was in charge of the rearguard at Cleaves Malice before the fort was overtaken.
InProgressResponse: Patricia has become twisted with Corruption.\n\nShe no longer deserves to have the cloak she received upon becoming a captain. And we can't allow her to keep her Heartgem.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Patricia's Heartgem…See Corruption swirling inside it? 

It finally feels real. She's really gone. 

She was once a fine Soulwarden, and someone very dear to me.

Title: Malice Aforethought
Description: Break the defenses of the Corrupted by attacking Cleaves Malice. Talk to Warden Phan in the Eastburn Outpost when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Someday, this wretched war with the Corrupted will end!\n\nIt's really taking a toll on us. The sooner we break their defenses, the sooner we can all get back to what really matters in life.
InProgressResponse: Help us break through the defensive line at Cleaves Malice.\n\nOur forces have taken bad losses, and those of us left need food and medicine to keep up our strength.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You caused a real commotion at Cleaves Malice, {playerName}! A few of our Rangers were able to slip through and deliver the supplies we needed. \n\nIt’s not a permanent fix, but it means we can keep fighting tomorrow!

Title: Descent to Frosted Slumber
Description: Slow the Corrupted by defeating Foreman Robertson and his Icefield workers. Talk to Watcher Chang in the Eastburn Outpost when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: We were expanding the village of Slumbering Echoes…that's where I'm from.\n\nWhen the Corrupted overran it, it was almost too easy for the Corrupted to come and take the lumber.
InProgressResponse: We need you to defeat the Foreman and his work crew.\n\nOur best strategy is to keep them from expanding their construction.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Nicely done! War is just as much about swinging hammers as swinging blades. \n\nNow that you’ve taken out the Foreman, their defenses are vulnerable. We can exploit that.

Title: All That's Left Not Torn Asunder
Description: Recover the Stolen Supplies from Sunderfort and deliver them to Soulwarden Phan in the Eastburn Outpost.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Right before Patricia’s betrayal, a shipment of our supplies was stolen by Corrupted and taken to Sunderfort. \n\nYou’ve been such a good distraction, they might not have had time to unload it yet.
InProgressResponse: Think of it! Dried fruit, or perhaps even dried fish... New weapons, more armor, fresh shot...!\n\nPlease, find whatever you can in Sunderfort! Anything extra would be helpful.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You were able to recover some of the supplies? That's a load off my mind. \n\nThe world might be ending, but at least we won't go hungry.

Title: Facets of Light and Darkness
Description: Recover Heartgems from the Valleyrend Corrupted in Sunderfort, and find clues about Corrupted activity in the area. Talk to Ranger Knatchbull in the Eastburn Outpost when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: We paid a steep price in the battle for Sunderfort. Many of our friends were lost. Even worse, Corruption still has them. \n\nI see them when I scout the fort: puppets with the faces of my comrades.
InProgressResponse: Aside from recovering those Heartgems, we need to find out what the Corrupted are doing at Sunderfort.\n\nThere has to be something keeping them there.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Yes, I recognize these Heartgems. I’ll give them to the Wardens for purification. 

As for me, it’s enough to know that they’re no longer tools of the enemy. 

That’s the best I can do for them, now.

Title: Transmuting Iron to Dust
Description: Slow the Corrupted war effort by defeating the Molderpick workers at the Defiler Excavation, and uncover the secret of the Corrupted ore. Talk to Watcher Chang in the Eastburn Outpost when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The Molderpick Corrupted have captured the old iron mine to the west. We’re calling it ‘Defiler Excavation’ now. \n\nBut the weird part is, we got our hands on some of the ore they’re mining there, and it’s...
InProgressResponse: If that ore is iron, it's the worst iron I've ever seen.\n\nWe need to find out more about it, and why the Molderpick workers want it.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You're back! Strange, this ore seems perfectly fine. Strong, even.\n\nAnd you say you found these vials throughout the mines? I wonder what happens when I pour it on the ore…

Title: Redefining Boundaries
Description: Collect Azoth Infused items from Catara Falls, Gelida Pillars, and Concretus Steps
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
Is this your first cleansing ritual? I envy you. 

Cleansing a Heartgem consumes azoth, a lot of it. But with all the Corruption here, there’s not enough ambient azoth to pull it off. 

We’ll need to get creative.
InProgressResponse: Catara Falls, Gelida Pillars, and Concretus Steps all have what we need to purify the Heartgems.\n\nWatch out for the Ancient Guardians, they mean business.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh, my, impressive! You've manage to gather all the materials we need to purify the Heartgems.\n\nThose Guardians didn't give you too much trouble, did they?

Title: The Ties That Blind
Description: Locate the missing Soulwarden Sexton, and report his whereabouts to Warden Dimka in the Cleave's Point Outpost.
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
Can I just say again how much I love your can-do attitude? 

Anyway, Warden Sexton went to deliver a message to Cleave’s Point, and he hasn’t come back. It’s not like him. 

Could you go find him?
InProgressResponse: With the losses we've suffered, every person is vital.\n\nNot to mention Soulwarden Dimka would be crushed to hear something happened to Sexton.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You have letters for me?\n\nOdd, I've never met you before and I think I would have remembered you.

Title: For A Rainy Day
Description: Recover the Secret Caches at Breakaway Fort and Acedia Bastion. Talk to Soulwarden Dimka in the Cleave's Point Outpost when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Please, don’t. You mean well, but the last thing I need right now is pity. \n\nJames…Warden Sexton…his letters weren’t all love letters. There’s a report in here that says that the Corrupted are stockpiling ammunition.
InProgressResponse: Breakaway Fort and Acedia Bastion have secret ammo caches located in false containers, and have likely buried some already.\n\nI don't want to think about James right now.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
What’s that? Oh, the ammunition. Sorry, I was miles away.

Yes, this is it. This ammunition should carry us through the next few raids.

Thank you, Soulwarden.

Title: Rainbow Hearts, Shadowed Intent
Description: Recover Soulwarden Heartgems from the Corrupted. Search for clues about the Corrupted plans in Breakaway Fort, Acedia Bastion, Hollowing Fort, and Nullcavity. Talk to Ranger Law in the Cleave's Point Outpost when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It’s… not ideal, no. It’s also not great that those forts are full of Corrupted Soulwardens. \n\nOur comrades and friends, who fought and fell beside us… They and the forts both belong to Corruption now.
InProgressResponse: Please, return with any Heartgems you can in Acedia Bastion, Breakaway Fort, Hollowing Fort, and Nullcavity.\n\nI hope you'll also find more evidence about what the Corrupted are up to, or even more of those strange symbols.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You brought back the Heartgems! Oh, wonderful. Now my friends won't be tortured anymore. \n\nYou also found… symbols? I’ve seen these before...the Corrupted carve them on the floating obelisks.

Title: A Burning Question
Description: Recover Azoth-Infused Lanterns from Miststride Ghouls in the Eeriedune Graveyard and Misty Borough. Talk to Watcher Owens in the Cleave's Point Outpost when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Have you heard of the ghost lights, the ignes fatui, the lanterns that flicker in the Eeriedune Graveyard?\n\nNever filled, never fueled, always burning? I need to learn more about their properties!
InProgressResponse: Return the lanterns to me, so I can uncover their secrets.\n\nThey are quite distinct, you should have no problem following their glow.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: The lanterns... There's no light, no glow, not even a flicker! Yet you say they are not broken...\n\nWhatever causes them to glow must come from the Ghouls themselves...

Title: Blessings of the Fallen
Description: Discover how Herald Abraxas blessed Misty Borough, and determine if the Heralds will aid the Soulwardens. Talk to Watcher Magoro in the Cleave's Point Outpost when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It does, doesn’t it? I’ve been hearing stories about the Misty Borough and Herald Abraxas since I was a child. He’s my hero. \n\nIf only we had someone like him on our side in this fight…the war would be over tomorrow!
InProgressResponse: If it's true, and the Herald's sacred power truly does protect his village from Corruption, perhaps we could use it across the island!\n\nHe could bless all of Great Cleave and drive the Corrupted right back into the mountain they crawled out of!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah! You're back! Will Herald Abraxas help us in the fight against the Corrupted?\n\nDid you discover how the hilltop is protected?

Title: Twisted Metamorphosis
Description: Defeat Gravespoil Vicars in Capitulum Prime, and return the stolen Heartgems to Watcher Owens in the Cleave's Point Outpost.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, both! Rangers have reported the theft of a cache of Corrupted Heartgems. The same Heartgems you recovered from our former comrades at the fallen forts! \n\nI knew we shouldn’t have kept them all in one place…
InProgressResponse: We can't let the Gravespoil Vicars use those Heartgems in their rituals.\nThose were our friends, and we owe it to them to keep their souls safe!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You’re back! Did you recover the Heartgems? Or were we too late?

Title: The Best of Us
Description: Defeat former Soulwarden Sauquillo Dimka, and return her Heartgem to Watcher Magoro in the Cleave's Point Outpost.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Ever since you brought the news of Sexton’s death…and, um, romantic betrayal…Dimka couldn’t take it. She was so sad, and angry, and embarrassed…in her despair, Corruption took her.
InProgressResponse: I’m sorry to ask for your help once again, but…you seem so strong. And you didn’t know Dimka like we did. Maybe that will make this easier. \n\nPlease, bring back her Heartgem. She deserves that much.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: That's Dimka’s Heartgem. It's hard to believe that she's gone…\n\nShe was brilliant, kind, vibrant... and now, she's some twisted and Corrupted thing. Is this the fate that awaits us all?

Title: The Winding Mountain Path
Description: Deliver Orders to Soulwarden Ducquet of Valor Hold Outpost in Edengrove. Talk to Warden Yseult in Shattered Mountain when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: If you're willing to continue helping the Soulwardens, there's another place that could really use it.\n\nIn Edengrove is the Valor Hold Outpost. They’re in the belly of the beast over there.
InProgressResponse: Remember, stick to the path.\n\nSoulwarden Ducquet will certainly be surprised to see you... I don't believe they've had outside news in months.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Your compass is backwards if you're heading for safety. You want safety, head for the coasts!\n\nOrders from Soulwarden Owens? Let's have a look then…

Title: Prime Resolve
Description: Gather supplies for Ranger Law to make Prime Resolve.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Here in Aeternum, where doom haunts our every move, we must hang on to the things that make us feel alive.\n\nTo that end, there is a legend we tell in Great Cleave that warms our hearts.
InProgressResponse: Isn’t fire wonderful? It keeps us warm, cooks our food, burns away the darkness and the filth and the pain… \n\nOnce you craft your own fire staff, you’ll understand.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: At last, Prime Resolve is completed. It’s beautiful. Truly a force to be reckoned with!\n\nKnowing you wield it will keep me warm during my cold patrols.

Title: Growth From the Stem
Description: Gather a Pulsing Staff Stem from Corrupted at Scorpius.

Title: Funnelling In
Description: Gather Vortex Funnel from Corrupted at Svikin's Stand.

Title: Flamestarters
Description: Gather Flint Flamestarters from Undead at Periville.

Title: Reagent Retrieval
Description: Gather Blistering Reagents from Corrupted at Greater Tribulation.

Title: Head of the Pack
Description: Gather a Curved Staffhead from Angry Earth at Eridanus.

Title: Swirling Staff Base
Description: Gather a Swirling Staff Base from Angry Earth at Malevolence.

Title: Flintlock
Description: Gather Orichalcum Flintlock from Undead Pirates at Stone Skull Fort.

Title: Requiring Concentration
Description: Defeat High Priest Oseguera in the Mangled Heights for an Azoth Concentrator.

Title: Glimmering Mercy
Description: Gather the parts, wholesome and true, for a life-giving staff made whole. Glittering, gleaming, restore and renew the Glimmering Mercy's soul. Talk to Ranger Madaki in Shattered Mountain when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: That place has eaten many careless Soulwardens. Your accomplishment is impressive…to some. \n\nBut no one triumphs alone, do they? I’ve heard you’ve been getting help from my friend Madaki in Shattered Mountain.
InProgressResponse: Getting lost in song is quite easy, which explains Rochford. Maybe I myself should follow his tune a little more!\n\nIf you're confused on your path, check the scribbled notes in your Journal and follow the symphony.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So, you've learned the Symphony of Mercy? I won't pretend to know the work of musicians, but I can at least whistle a tune as I work.\n\nGive me a moment to extract the essences I need, and I'll finish crafting the Mercy.

Title: Prelude of the Acolytes
Description: Blood-stained robes and cursed staves, nefarious acolytes raise their minions forth. Find them in the heights west by north, and send them to their cursed graves.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @0320_0102_Prelude_complete_available_response

Title: The Wyrdwood Adagio
Description: Weeping trees, they be not willow nor withe, growing wild in the winding way. Survive the wanton whaling of the forestwalkers, and your woes be rewarded with the trees' blue tears.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @0320_0103_Adagio_complete_available_response

Title: Shaman's Scherzo
Description: Another place, another body, another time, the wisest of shamans are not of here but a reality that bends. The myrrh they carry is their vehicle, the key to a magic that transcends.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @0320_0104_Scherzo_complete_available_response

Title: The Stone Skull Shanty
Description: One swig for courage, two swigs to sleep, three swigs to settle your strife, and four swigs when under the knife. Give me that bottom of the barrel wine, freshly butchered swine, and a wench for a good time.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @0320_0105_Shanty_complete_available_response

Title: Zarabanda del Ojo Rojo
Description: The red eye of the bay, the red eye of the bay, the tower calling sailors to their doom. Deep in the tower, hidden away, an ancient and powerful rune.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @0320_0106_Zarabanda_complete_available_response

Title: Requiem for the Lost
Description: Temporary forms made immortal and pinned to the earth in sorrow. The faithless turn their back on the path.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @0320_0107_Requiem_complete_available_response

Title: Passepied de la Tour
Description: In the heart of the craters, the soul of Aeternum, climb towards the sky. Peek into the mirror and learn the ways of those that defend the tower.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @0320_0108_Passepied_complete_available_response

Title: Sonata of the Shattered
Description: Dive into the belly of the beast, and the heart of Corruption. Though light may cast out the darkness, it in turn casts a shadow.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @0320_0109_Sonata_complete_available_response

Title: Forging the Azure Ravager
Description: Recover the components needed to create the Azure Ravager, and deliver them to Ranger Madaki in Mountainhome.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I know. I started seeing the influx of strange items coming into the forts nearby, and I didn't question her any longer.\n\nSomething unusual was going on, so I started to look into it.
InProgressResponse: I’d love to join you, but I have other duties. I have to try and stop any more of those supplies from reaching the forges in Caminus.\n\nI’m sure you can find all the items on that list by yourself!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Glad you made it back. Wow, some of this stuff must have been hard to find. Nicely done.\n\nGive me a bit to integrate these last components you've brought, and we'll see what we end up with.

Title: Death and Taxes
Description: Collect a Starmetal Whetstone from Brightwood Isle.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: By Root and Bough
Description: Collect the Rubble from the bodies of Dryad Archers in Eridanus, and obtain an Evergreen Dryad Branch from their leader.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: A Sample of Evil
Description: Locate Corruption Breaches throughout Aeternum, and cut down the hordes of Monstrous Corrupted who gather there.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: Crystallized Corruption
Description: Deep within Scorpius, take back the Desecrated Azoth Crystal from S'ylanx the Unseen
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: Shards From Above and Below
Description: Find samples of Tainted Orichalcum and collect Everburning Embers from Ambusti Superior. Talk to Ranger Madaki in Shattered Mountain when the task is done.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: It looks like you've made a lot of progress already! I've been working to alter this recipe to channel azoth instead of Corruption... and with what you've brought me, I think I'll be able to make this work.

Title: Wooden Hearts and Iron Heads
Description: Collect Corrupted Iron Hammerheads from the Elite Southguard Forgers of Svikin's Stand.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: There are still a few more items on Fowler's shopping list, and I still have a lot to do to make sure this Hatchet won't do anything crazy, like try and suck your soul out.\n\nKidding... I think.
InProgressResponse: You bring me the components, and I'll get this thing made. The faster you bring everything back, the faster you can use this weapon on those damned Corrupted.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: Sticking to the Plan
Description: Seek out Unstable Azoth Shards and Ethereal Adhesive from the Lost of Periville.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: The Gleaming Edge
Description: Collect Drowned Silver Coins hoarded by the Skullworm Pirates of Stone Skull Fort. Talk to Ranger Fowler in Great Cleave when the task is complete.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: A great haul, wonderfully done! While you've been out, I was able to stop three other shipments from making their way to the forges of Caminus.\n\nFelt good to be up and active, you know?

Title: The Rampant Conviction of Hope
Description: Recover the components needed to create the Rampant Conviction, then deliver them to Ranger Madaki in Mountainhome.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I've received her instructions, and have set my efforts to stopping the production of Corrupted weapons.\n\nTo that end, I've compiled reports to track the weapons that have recently passed through the valley.
InProgressResponse: Be watchful, stick to the shadows, and don’t move until you need to. This tactic has served me well over the years. \n\nIt will serve you too, if you embrace it.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Didn't get too lost out there, I hope?\n\nLet's take a look at what you brought me, hm? Oh, yes... these will do nicely for what's needed.

Title: Unbalanced Scales
Description: Collect Pirate Token Pouches from the Elite Grubby Rebels of Stone Skull Fort, and recover Goldstein's Scales from Goldstein the Equalizer.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: Piercing the Veil
Description: Obtain Veil Leather from the Corrupted throughout Scorpius.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: Bones of the Past
Description: Retrieve bone dust from caskets in Periville
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: The Forest's Heart
Description: Obtain Vinesnap's Heart from within Eridanus, and collect Dryad Fighter Vines from the Eridanite Dryads.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: Filament and Firmament
Description: Collect a stalk from an Elite Unhallowed Tendrils in the Mangled Heights.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: Into the Burning Depths
Description: Retrieve Contaminated Ore from chests in Ambusti Superior.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: A Vile Harvest
Description: Locate Corruption Breaches throughout Aeternum, and cut down the hordes of Monstrous Corrupted who gather there.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: The Living Crystal
Description: Obtain the Living Crystal from the monstrous Dryad at the peak of Malevolence. Talk to Ranger Knatchbull in the Eastburn Outpost when the task is complete.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Great work, {playerName}. I haven’t been idle either. \n\nEight caravans attempted to bring additional supplies through the valley…they will not reach their destinations.

Title: Hand of Hoarfrost
Description: Gather components to make the Legendary Ice Gauntlet Rimelash.
PlayerPrompt: "You aren't just talking about the weather..."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Just think of it, holding the power of a snowstorm in one's hand. \n\nThere's a weapon that allows for this and more, the gauntlet Rimelash. With it you can freeze enemies and shatter their frozen forms.
InProgressResponse: This land is full of shifting forces greater than all of us. But we won’t be afraid. We will master them, in time. \n\nGo, master the power of winter, and bring Rimelash into the world once more.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: What a resounding success! I present to you: Rimelash, the instrument of icy destruction that will freeze and fell your enemies before they even know what's hit them!

Title: Blood in the Snow
Description: Gather the Corrupted Bindings that will hold together the gauntlet from Legatus General Patrick at Svikin's Stand. Talk to Ranger Madaki at Shattered Mountain.

Title: Aeternum's Icy Crown
Description: Gather the Frozen Orichalcum Plating from the frozen crown of North Myrkgard, Greater Tribulation.

Title: Wintry Boons
Description: Gather the Chilled Fungi that grows upon the Elite Alcazarian Guardians of Malevolence for an extra kick of frost.

Title: Frozen Heart
Description: Kill Corrupted on the way to gather S'ylanx the Unseen's frozen, twisted heart to make a core for the gauntlet.

Title: Forged in Frost
Description: Gather Frostforged Grips to make up the hand of the gauntlet from the Corrupted of Caminus.

Title: Chilling Spectres
Description: Gather Everbite Ectoplasm from the wraiths of frigid Periville, their cold everlasting in undeath.

Title: Rebels on Ice
Description: Gather Icy Shot from the Skullworm Pirates of Stone Skull Fort, a special ammunition they keep on them for inflicting maximum pain.

Title: Frostbitten Fighters
Description: Defeat Dryads and their leader Parthenocissus for his Frostbitten Vine that will wrap around the core of the gauntlet.
